{{Infobox physical quantity | bgcolour={default} | name = Specific potential energy | image = | caption = | basequantities = m<sup>2</sup>/s<sup>2</sup> | unit = J/kg | symbols = pe, or ''e''<sub>u</sub> | derivations = ''e''<sub>u</sub> = ''[[Gravitational_acceleration|g]]'' [[height|h]] }}
'''Specific potential energy''' is [[potential energy]] of an object per unit of mass of that object.
In a gravitational field it is the acceleration of gravity times height, <math>e_u=gh</math>.
